=List of Dutch organizations=

* [[New Explorers Guide to Dutch Digital Culture]]: a clear overview of the major players in the field of digital art and culture in the Netherlands. Get in touch with over 150 organisations, categorised in media labs, media festivals and game companies. [http://virtueelplatform.nl/g/content/download/the-new-explorers-guide-to-dutch-digital-culture-2.pdf pdf]

#Accessibility.nl - making ICT available to people with disabilities
#AMS-ix - the largest internet exchange on the planet
#Bendeburgers - e-participation platform
#Bits of Freedom - protecting online civil rights
#Dutch Hosting Provider Association - association of hosting companies
#Eth0 - hacker association
#Free Knowledge Institute - promotes free knowledge and software
#Fronteers - association of front end developers
#Gridforum.nl - association for grid and cloud professionals
#Het Nieuwe Stemmen - making society open with open data
#Holland Open - open source software, open standards, open content
#Hxx - hacker association
#ISPconnect - association of Internet Service Providers
#Internet Society Nederland - to promote the free, robust and reliable internet
#NLnet - charity that invests in open technologies
#NLnet Labs - R&D on core internet technology
#OpenDoc Society - knowledge platform around open document formats
#RIPE NCC - Regional Internet Registry (RIR)
#SIDN - the organisation behind .nl and ENUM in the Netherlands
#SURFnet - national research and education network
#Terena - Trans-European Research and Education Networking Association
#Vereniging Open Domein - promotes public domain on the internet
#Vrijschrift - striving for free information and protection of privacy
#W3C Benelux - the Benelux office of the webstandards organisation

